CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1958, pg. A12, reads: "The FROGS Have Fun - Frog Week opened last Sunday with a gay party for members, their wives and out-of-town guests at the Terrain Room of Terrace Hall.  The above pictures tell the story of how the Frogs and their guests had fun.  Top left photo shows three charming out-of-town guests enjoying some of the festive fare.  Left to right: Mrs. Romaine Dennings Lyons of Los Angeles, Calif.; Mrs. Erma Roy, Baltimore, Md., and Miss Carrie Warley of Lookout, Tenn. ... - All Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Romaine Dennings Lyons, Erma Roy, and Carrie Warley selecting food from buffet table at FROGS week party in Terrain Room of Terrace Hall
